com.b2international.snowowl.core.branch

Interface Branch

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Deletable, MetadataHolder, java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BranchData

    public interface Branch
extends Deletable, MetadataHolder, java.io.Serializable
    Represents a Branch in a terminology repository. A Branch can be uniquely identified by using its path() and baseTimestamp() values.
    Since:
    4.1

      • rebase

        Branch rebase(Branch onTopOf,
              java.lang.String commitMessage)
        Rebases this branch Branch on top of the specified Branch.

        Rebasing this branch does not actually modify this Branch state, instead it will create a new Branch representing the rebased form of this Branch and returns it. Commits available on the target Branch will be available on the resulting Branch after successful rebase.

        Parameters:
        onTopOf - - the branch on top of which this branch should be lifted
        commitMessage - - the commit message
        Returns:
